Jamaica Ave., at the N.E. corner of Fanchon Place, showing Tubbs Hotel (later in the 1870's it was known as Chris. Koch's Hotel, after many years, it became known as Cavaluzzo's Cafe. It was demolished in 1929).

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
